Trunk of right middle cerebral artery

definition.value: Organ component of neuraxis that has as its parts the telencephalon, diencephalon, lateral ventricles and third ventricle. Examples: There is only one forebrain.
Organ component of neuraxis that has as its parts the tectum, cerebral peduncle, midbrain tegmentum  and cerebral aqueduct. Examples: There is only one midbrain.

label.value: Set of cortical branches of insular zone of right middle cerebral artery
Set of lenticulostriate branches of sphenoid zone of right middle cerebral artery
Trunk of sphenoid part of middle cerebral artery
Communicating branch of phrenic nerve to internal thoracic plexus

definition.value: Organ component of neuraxis that has as its parts the cerebral cortex, cerebral white matter, basal ganglia, septum and fornix, as well as subcortical gray and white matter structures.  There is only one telencephalon.
Organ component of neuraxis that has as its parts the epithalamus, thalamus, hypothalamus, subthalamus. There is only one diencephalon.

label.value: Trunk of insular part of middle cerebral artery

definition.value: Rostral segment of the hindbrain that has as its parts the pons and the cerebellum.

Organ component of neuraxis that has as its parts the medullary reticular formation, inferior olivary complex and cochlear nuclear complex, among other structures. Examples: There is only one medulla oblongata.

label.value: Branch of phrenic nerve to mediastinal pleura
